This paper is about generative models, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper proposes a new family of prior distributions that can be used in GANs and VAEs, which are popular generative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound).
